20070914	O

FPAY	O
+	O
FEE	O
PAYMENT	O
N	O
US	O
6065016A	O
8	O

BACKGROUND	O
OF	O
THE	O
INVENTION	O
This	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
directory	O
services	O
.	O
More	O
particularly	O
,	O
this	O
invention	O
relates	O
to	O
a	O
directory	O
service	O
which	O
provides	O
the	O
communication	O
addresses	O
of	O
individuals	O
associated	O
with	O
numerous	O
different	O
institutions	O
,	O
and	O
which	O
can	O
be	O
accessed	O
via	O
more	O
than	O
one	O
communication	O
channel	O
.	O

Due	O
to	O
the	O
rapid	O
growth	O
in	O
on-line	O
and	O
wireless	O
technology	O
,	O
many	O
individuals	O
today	O
(	O
especially	O
white-collar	O
professionals	O
)	O
can	O
be	O
reached	O
at	O
numerous	O
communications	O
addresses	O
.	O
An	O
individual	O
's	O
communication	O
addresses	O
may	O
include	O
a	O
business	O
telephone	O
number	O
,	O
a	O
home	O
telephone	O
number	O
,	O
a	O
fax	O
number	O
,	O
a	O
cellular	O
telephone	O
number	O
,	O
a	O
pager	O
number	O
,	O
a	O
personal	O
reach	O
service	O
number	O
,	O
an	O
e-mail	O
address	O
,	O
a	O
home	O
page	O
URL	O
,	O
a	O
personal	O
communications	O
service	O
(	O
PCS	O
)	O
number	O
,	O
and	O
a	O
secretary/reach	O
telephone	O
number	O
.	O

Obtaining	O
this	O
information	O
for	O
a	O
particular	O
individual	O
can	O
be	O
difficult	O
and	O
time	O
consuming	O
.	O
Often	O
,	O
several	O
sources	O
must	O
be	O
consulted	O
before	O
the	O
desired	O
information	O
is	O
tracked	O
down	O
,	O
forcing	O
one	O
to	O
make	O
repeated	O
attempts	O
to	O
locate	O
the	O
information	O
.	O
This	O
can	O
be	O
time	O
consuming	O
and	O
potentially	O
costly	O
,	O
especially	O
if	O
the	O
person	O
is	O
far	O
away	O
or	O
in	O
another	O
country	O
.	O
Sometimes	O
the	O
information	O
appears	O
on	O
business	O
cards	O
,	O
but	O
one	O
often	O
does	O
not	O
have	O
the	O
necessary	O
business	O
card	O
at-hand	O
when	O
attempting	O
to	O
reach	O
a	O
person	O
.	O
Furthermore	O
,	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
ways	O
to	O
reach	O
someone	O
has	O
become	O
so	O
large	O
that	O
business	O
cards	O
have	O
become	O
cumbersome	O
,	O
awkward	O
,	O
unattractive	O
,	O
and	O
confusing	O
.	O

Currently	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
no	O
centralized	O
directory	O
service	O
which	O
provides	O
a	O
person	O
's	O
numerous	O
communications	O
addresses	O
.	O
Furthermore	O
,	O
there	O
is	O
no	O
centralized	O
directory	O
service	O
which	O
provides	O
all	O
of	O
the	O
communication	O
addresses	O
of	O
individuals	O
associated	O
with	O
different	O
companies	O
.	O
The	O
list	O
of	O
phone	O
numbers	O
contained	O
in	O
local	O
"	O
white	O
pages	O
"	O
directories	O
is	O
typically	O
limited	O
to	O
home	O
and	O
front-desk	O
business	O
numbers	O
.	O
Some	O
corporations	O
and	O
universities	O
maintain	O
on-line	O
directories	O
which	O
are	O
accessible	O
via	O
the	O
internet	O
.	O
However	O
,	O
these	O
directories	O
provide	O
limited	O
information	O
such	O
as	O
a	O
primary	O
telephone	O
number	O
and	O
e-mail	O
address	O
.	O
Some	O
companies	O
,	O
such	O
as	O
AT&T	O
,	O
maintain	O
internal	O
directories	O
which	O
can	O
only	O
be	O
accessed	O
by	O
employees	O
.	O
AT&T	O
's	O
internal	O
directory	O
provides	O
the	O
telephone	O
number	O
,	O
FAX	O
number	O
,	O
e-mail	O
address	O
,	O
and	O
mailing	O
address	O
of	O
certain	O
individuals	O
associated	O
with	O
AT&T	O
,	O
among	O
other	O
information	O
such	O
as	O
company	O
organizational	O
information	O
and	O
the	O
individual	O
's	O
work	O
location	O
and	O
room	O
number	O
.	O

Looking	O
for	O
the	O
communication	O
addresses	O
of	O
individuals	O
associated	O
with	O
different	O
companies	O
using	O
on-line	O
directories	O
maintained	O
by	O
corporations	O
and	O
other	O
institutions	O
can	O
be	O
time	O
consuming	O
for	O
several	O
reasons	O
.	O
First	O
,	O
one	O
has	O
to	O
determine	O
the	O
e-mail	O
address	O
of	O
the	O
particular	O
institution	O
where	O
the	O
desired	O
information	O
resides	O
.	O
Second	O
,	O
such	O
directories	O
may	O
not	O
have	O
the	O
particular	O
communication	O
address	O
one	O
is	O
looking	O
for	O
.	O
Third	O
,	O
one	O
is	O
required	O
to	O
access	O
a	O
separate	O
on-line	O
directory	O
for	O
each	O
company	O
,	O
which	O
can	O
be	O
tedious	O
and	O
time	O
consuming	O
when	O
searching	O
for	O
the	O
numbers	O
of	O
several	O
individuals	O
employed	O
at	O
different	O
companies	O
.	O

In	O
view	O
of	O
these	O
and	O
other	O
drawbacks	O
of	O
current	O
directory	O
services	O
,	O
it	O
is	O
an	O
object	O
of	O
this	O
invention	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
directory	O
service	O
that	O
enables	O
a	O
user	O
to	O
obtain	O
from	O
a	O
centralized	O
location	O
the	O
communication	O
addresses	O
of	O
individuals	O
from	O
numerous	O
different	O
institutions	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
a	O
more	O
particular	O
object	O
of	O
this	O
invention	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
directory	O
service	O
which	O
provides	O
all	O
of	O
the	O
communication	O
addresses	O
of	O
an	O
individual	O
in	O
a	O
centralized	O
location	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
a	O
still	O
more	O
particular	O
object	O
of	O
this	O
invention	O
to	O
provide	O
a	O
directory	O
service	O
which	O
provides	O
supplemental	O
information	O
in	O
addition	O
to	O
an	O
individual	O
's	O
communications	O
addresses	O
.	O

It	O
is	O
a	O
further	O
object	O
of	O
this	O
invention	O
to	O
